100
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:37,580
can make a significant difference.
能实现显著的改变

101
00:06:40,780 --> 00:06:42,370
Ralph Waldo Emerson:
爱默生说

102
00:06:43,230 --> 00:06:46,740
"All history is a record of the power of minorities,
"人类历史是少数派

103
00:06:46,740 --> 00:06:48,850
and of minorities of one,
和一个人的少数派的权力记录

104
00:06:49,740 --> 00:06:52,970
"-- a lot to backed that up in social science research.
很多社会科学研究支持这个观点

105
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:56,040
Margaret Mead, the anthropologist:
人类学家Margaret Mead说

106
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:58,110
"Never doubt that a small group of thoughtful,
"永远不要怀疑一小群

107
00:06:58,110 --> 00:07:00,500
committed citizens can change the world.
有思想 坚定的市民可以改变世界

108
00:07:00,500 --> 00:07:04,070
Indeed, it is the only thing that ever has."
事实上 正是这群人改变着世界"

109
00:07:04,070 --> 00:07:08,450
All change begins in the mind of single person or a small group."
所有改变从一个人或一小众人的思想开始

110
00:07:08,850 --> 00:07:10,050
And then it expands.
然后不断扩大

111
00:07:10,050 --> 00:07:12,520
Now the question is "how does it expand"
问题是"它如何扩大"

112
00:07:12,520 --> 00:07:15,420
and "why is it so difficult for us to understand,
以及为什么我们难以理解

113
00:07:15,420 --> 00:07:18,280
accept, assimilate and live according to the fact
我们能够做出改变这个事实

114
00:07:18,280 --> 00:07:22,230
that we can make a difference,
