加州人不比麻省人更快乐

536
00:30:18,650 --> 00:30:21,300
Initially when we go to a warm place,
刚去到一个温暖的地方

537
00:30:21,300 --> 00:30:24,630
we feel the relief and there's this spiky level of wellbeing.
会感到放松 幸福水平高到值峰

538
00:30:25,170 --> 00:30:28,080
But very quickly we go back to our base level
但很快我们会恢复基础水平

539
00:30:28,080 --> 00:30:31,410
exactly where we were before.
和以前的我们一模一样

540
00:30:32,770 --> 00:30:34,110
I'll take this even a step further,
我会进一步说明

541
00:30:34,110 --> 00:30:36,780
even though there is no research about this,
虽然还没有这方面的研究

542
00:30:36,780 --> 00:30:38,680
I bet you this is correct:
我敢和你们打赌 下面的说法是正确的

543
00:30:38,680 --> 00:30:41,750
there is no difference in our levels of wellbeing
我们的幸福水平不会有所不同

544
00:30:42,670 --> 00:30:47,050
if our place of residents is by the river
不论我们是生活在河边

545
00:30:48,730 --> 00:30:51,530
or in the quad.
还是呆在quad （哈佛举行毕业典礼等重大集会的地方）

546
00:30:51,960 --> 00:30:55,800
This is really taking the theory far, but it's true.
这个例子把理论推至极限 但是真的

547
00:30:57,430 --> 00:30:58,510
I love this T-shirt-- what?
我喜欢这件衬衫 什么?

548
00:30:58,510 --> 00:31:01,690
If you can't run with the big dogs, stay in yard.
不能和大狗一起跑就呆在院子里

549
00:31:01,690 --> 00:31:05,190
Anyone from Korea here? Alright.
这里有韩国学生吗?好的

550
00:31:08,200 --> 00:31:10,160
You made it all the way on such a cold day.
你在这么冷的日子赶来

551
00:31:10,160 --> 00:31:12,030
Well done! I appreciated it.
很出色 我很感激

552
00:31:14,440 --> 00:31:19,420
How spoiled we get here. Makes very little difference.
我们真是受宠若惊 不会有所不同

553
00:31:19,420 --> 00:31:21,530
Very little difference--
微乎甚微的区别

554
00:31:22,390 --> 00:31:24,860
where we are, where we live,
我们在哪里 我们生活在哪里

555
00:31:24,860 --> 00:31:27,820
income levels, lottery, tenure,
收入水平 是否中彩票 是否取得终身职位

556
00:31:28,050 --> 00:31:30,800
getting into our dream college,
入读理想中大学

557
00:31:30,800 --> 00:31:33,310
getting our dream job for you seniors--
找到理想工作 大四学生

558
00:31:33,310 --> 00:31:34,860
you may have just gotten it.
可能已经找到

559
00:31:37,090 --> 00:31:39,140
Yeah, you are going to have a spike in your level of wellbeing--
没错 你们会感觉极至的幸福

560
00:31:39,140 --> 00:31:41,070
I'm sure you had a spike in your level of wellbeing
我肯定拿到录取信时

561
00:31:41,070 --> 00:31:43,150
when you got this acceptance letter,
你们的幸福感也达到峰值

562
00:31:43,300 --> 00:31:45,990
but very quickly we go back to our base level.
但很快又恢复到基础水平

563
00:31:48,520 --> 00:31:51,520
One thing that does matter to our base level of wellbeing
对基础幸福水平很重要的一样东西

564
00:31:51,520 --> 00:31:57,880
which is external circumstance is democracy versus oppression.
它是一个外在因素 那就是民主和压迫

565
00:31:57,880 --> 00:32:00,760
People living in democracies are generally significantly
生活在民主制度下的人通常明显

566
00:32:00,760 --> 00:32:03,830
happier than people living in dictatorships.
比生活在独裁制度下的人更快乐

567
00:32:05,490 --> 00:32:06,510
Women, for example,
以女性为例

568
00:32:06,510 --> 00:32:09,450
living in places where they are oppressed are in general
生活在压迫制度下的一般

569
00:32:09,450 --> 00:32:12,650
less happy than women living in free countries.
没有生活在自由国家的女性快乐

570
00:32:13,010 --> 00:32:16,020
People living in Darfur are certainly
生活在达尔福尔的人

571
00:32:16,020 --> 00:32:21,650
less happy than people living in Denmark or the United States.
肯定没有生活在丹麦或美国的人快乐

572
00:32:23,380 --> 00:32:25,680
But again, these are the extreme circumstance
这些是能产生区别的

573
00:32:25,680 --> 00:32:27,740
that do make a difference,
极端情况

574
00:32:27,740 --> 00:32:29,600
such as I said, a homeless person,
比如我举的无家可归者的例子

575
00:32:29,750 --> 00:32:32,550
of course, income will make a difference to that person.
收入当然会改善他的境遇

576
00:32:33,460 --> 00:32:34,600
Moving to a free country,
移民到自由国家

577
00:32:34,600 --> 00:32:36,660
of course, will make a difference to their wellbeing.
当然会让他们更加幸福

578
00:32:36,660 --> 00:32:38,640
But beyond the extremes,
但在这些极端情况之外

579
00:32:40,020 --> 00:32:43,040
additions or subtractions to our external circumstances
增加或减少的外部环境

580
00:32:43,040 --> 00:32:45,340
make very little difference.
产生的区别很小

581
00:32:45,340 --> 00:32:50,770
Now this is good news and bad news.
这即是好消息也是坏消息

582
00:32:51,420 --> 00:32:55,000
The bad news is it seems like whatever we do,
坏消息是 看来不论我们怎么做

583
00:32:55,000 --> 00:32:55,840
it doesn't matter.
都无关紧要

584
00:32:55,840 --> 00:33:00,740
So why am I working hard in order to get that BCG job?
我为什么还要努力争取好工作？

585
00:33:01,660 --> 00:33:06,850
why did I work so hard in order to get into this place?
我为什么要拼命入读这所学校

586
00:33:07,420 --> 00:33:10,820
If it doesn't matter, if I experience this ups and downs.
如果这些都无关紧要 总要经历高低潮?

587
00:33:12,890 --> 00:33:14,130
And the answer is that--
答案是

588
00:33:14,130 --> 00:33:16,520
yes it won't make a difference to our wellbeing
是的 它不会改变我们的幸福水平

589
00:33:17,190 --> 00:33:18,590
but it also doesn't mean that
但并不意味着

590
00:33:18,590 --> 00:33:21,710
we cannot increase our level of wellbeing.
我们不能提升自己的幸福水平

591
00:33:22,020 --> 00:33:23,940
Many people said the problem
很多人说

592
00:33:23,940 --> 00:33:27,470
with general levels of happiness or unhappiness rather,
一般的快乐或不快乐水平

593
00:33:27,470 --> 00:33:31,240
the cause is people have too high expectations.
是由于人们有过高的期望

594
00:33:31,550 --> 00:33:33,310
And if we lower our expectations,
如果能降低期望

595
00:33:33,310 --> 00:33:37,930
we lower our stress levels and we will enjoy life more.
降低压力水平 我们会更享受生活

596
00:33:37,930 --> 00:33:41,560
"Ok, so I don't care if I don't get a B in the course.
我不在乎成绩是不是B

597
00:33:41,560 --> 00:33:43,650
I'd be much happier if I don't care,
不在乎会让我更快乐

598
00:33:43,650 --> 00:33:45,800
if I lower my levels of expectation.
如果我降低期望水平

599
00:33:45,800 --> 00:33:47,840
I don't care what I get into, what job I have,
我不在乎从事什么工作

600
00:33:47,840 --> 00:33:49,430
I just want to be happy."
只想快乐

601
00:33:49,430 --> 00:33:50,700
And you'll probably be happy.
你可能会快乐

602
00:33:50,700 --> 00:33:53,440
Slightly happy if you lower your levels of expectations,
降低期望水平会略微快乐些

603
00:33:53,440 --> 00:33:55,720
but not in the long term.
但从长远来说行不通

604
00:33:55,720 --> 00:33:57,900
And we'll talk about it next week.
下周我们会谈到这个问题

605
00:33:57,900 --> 00:33:59,290
Not in the long term.
长远来说行不通

606
00:34:00,310 --> 00:34:03,790
The problem is not lower these high expectations--
问题不在于是否降低那些高的期望

607
00:34:03,790 --> 00:34:05,370
that doesn't matter.
这一点不重要

608
00:34:05,370 --> 00:34:10,150
The problem is right versus wrong expectations.
问题在于正确和错误的期望

609
00:34:11,190 --> 00:34:13,500
Not lower high expectations--
而不是低的和高的期望

610
00:34:13,500 --> 00:34:15,870
that won't make a difference to our levels of wellbeing.
那不会影响我们的幸福水平

611
00:34:16,210 --> 00:34:19,730
What will make a difference to our levels of wellbeing
能影响幸福水平的

612
00:34:19,730 --> 00:34:23,560
is if we have right vs. wrong expectations.
是我们的期望是正确还是错误

613
00:34:23,560 --> 00:34:28,270
It is wrong expectation to expect that getting into a certain place,
错误的期望认为进入某间公司

614
00:34:28,270 --> 00:34:29,800
getting a raise,
获得升职

615
00:34:35,180 --> 00:34:37,740
finding our dream partner,
找到理想的伴侣

616
00:34:38,660 --> 00:34:41,540
is responsible for our happiness.
就能让自己更快乐

617
00:34:41,940 --> 00:34:47,610
Moving to California or to (Forts Heimer?).
搬去加州或哈默堡

618
00:34:48,410 --> 00:34:51,280
That in and of itself will not make us happier.
这本身不会让我们更快乐

619
00:34:53,480 --> 00:34:54,510
That's wrong expectation.
那是错误的期望

620
00:34:54,510 --> 00:35:00,470
The right expectation is to believe in change from within.
正确的期望是相信内在的改变

621
00:35:00,470 --> 00:35:03,370
So these things will not make us happy.
这些事情不会让我们快乐

622
00:35:03,690 --> 00:35:07,190
In fact, our readiness and potential to experience happiness
事实上 我们的准备和体验幸福的可能性

623
00:35:07,190 --> 00:35:09,440
is mostly depended on our state of mind,
主要由我们的心境决定

624
00:35:09,440 --> 00:35:13,760
not on our status, or the states of our bank account.
不是我们的地位或银行账户状况

625
00:35:14,300 --> 00:35:17,620
It's about changing our perception-- state of mind.
我们要改变我们的认知 心境

626
00:35:17,620 --> 00:35:22,050
It's about changing our interpretation of the world,
要改变我们对世界的诠释

627
00:35:22,490 --> 00:35:26,890
of what's happening to us, of our achievements, of our failures.
以及我们的遭遇 成就 失败

628
00:35:28,080 --> 00:35:29,910
It's about what we choose to perceive,
重要的是我们选择领悟什么

629
00:35:29,910 --> 00:35:31,390
what we choose to focus on.
精力集中的焦点是什么

630
00:35:31,390 --> 00:35:35,290
It's about transformation,
重要的是转变

631
00:35:35,290 --> 00:35:40,640
as opposed to the external information or the external success.
而不是外部信息或外部成功

632
00:35:41,930 --> 00:35:43,450
1504-- this whole course,
1504这门课程的重点

633
00:35:43,450 --> 00:35:45,720
is about this transformation,
是关于转变

634
00:35:45,720 --> 00:35:48,590
as I mentioned during the first lesson.
正如我在第一课中提到的

635
00:35:58,120 --> 00:36:00,630
I want to move on to the fourth premise,
我想进入第四个前提

636
00:36:00,630 --> 00:36:03,410
one of the most important premises in this course.
这堂课最重要的一个前提

637
00:36:03,410 --> 00:36:04,100
And in many ways,
在很多方面

638
00:36:04,100 --> 00:36:06,230
we can understand human intellectual history
我们能理解人类智力发展历史

639
00:36:06,230 --> 00:36:08,530
just based on this idea:
仅仅基于这个观点

640
00:36:09,270 --> 00:36:11,070
should we accept human nature?
应不应该接受人类本性?

641
00:36:11,450 --> 00:36:14,120
Or can we perfect it?
我们能否完善它?

642
00:36:14,120 --> 00:36:15,990
And can it change?
它能否改变?

643
00:36:15,990 --> 00:36:20,390
This work relies on--
这个工作或者说这些观点

644
00:36:20,730 --> 00:36:23,560
or these ideas rely on the work of Thomas Sowell.
基于Thomas Sowell的成果

645
00:36:23,560 --> 00:36:25,910
Thomas Sowell, Harvard class of 58,
Thomas Sowell 哈佛58届学生

646
00:36:26,280 --> 00:36:29,320
now at Stanford, the Hoover Institute,
目前就职斯坦福的胡佛研究院

647
00:36:29,320 --> 00:36:31,410
one of my intellectual heroes.
我心中的一位知识分子英雄

648
00:36:32,560 --> 00:36:37,320
And what he does and what his work does is basically explain
他的工作和作品的贡献在于解释了

649
00:36:37,320 --> 00:36:41,430
why people choose to back one political party versus the other;
人们为什么会选择一个党派反对另一个

650
00:36:41,430 --> 00:36:44,250
why they choose to live one kind of life versus the other.
为什么会选择一种生活方式摒弃另一种

651
00:36:44,250 --> 00:36:47,210
This single book helped me understand myself better
这本书帮助我更好地了解自己

652
00:36:47,210 --> 00:36:48,180
as well as other people better--
更好地了解别人

653
00:36:48,180 --> 00:36:49,310
whether it's politically,
不论是政治上

654
00:36:49,310 --> 00:36:52,090
whether it's psychologically, whether it's philosophically.
心理上还是哲学观上

655
00:36:52,480 --> 00:36:53,840
Those of you who are interested in politics
对政治感兴趣的同学

656
00:36:53,840 --> 00:36:55,810
and there is one book you want to read,
如果说有一本书是必读的

657
00:36:55,810 --> 00:36:59,360
after you read Marva Collins of course, it's this.
读完Marva Collins的作品后 就是这本

658
00:37:00,750 --> 00:37:03,140
So what does Thomas Sowell say?
Thomas Sowell所执的观点是什么？

659
00:37:03,140 --> 00:37:08,070
Essentially what he does is divide people into two camps
他把人分成两个阵营

660
00:37:08,070 --> 00:37:10,930
those who hold constrained vision,
那些认为本性受约束

661
00:37:11,520 --> 00:37:13,130
the limited vision;
有局限性的观点的人

662
00:37:13,130 --> 00:37:15,120
and those who hold the unconstrained,
和认为人性不受约束

663
00:37:15,120 --> 00:37:19,840
the unlimited vision of human nature.
无局限性的观点的人

664
00:37:19,840 --> 00:37:24,210
People who hold constrained vision of human nature,
认为人性受约束的观点的人

665
00:37:24,210 --> 00:37:26,960
believe that human nature cannot be changed;
相信人性无法改变

666
00:37:26,960 --> 00:37:29,300
it's immutable-- we have certain instincts,
它是永恒的 我们有一些本能

667
00:37:29,300 --> 00:37:30,980
we have certain inclinations.
有一些欲望

668
00:37:30,980 --> 00:37:33,390
They are fixed. This is it.
它们是固有的 无法改变

669
00:37:33,390 --> 00:37:34,570
What you see is what you get.
是什么样就是什么样

670
00:37:34,570 --> 00:37:36,570
What you are born with or were born with,
作为人的物种

671
00:37:36,570 --> 00:37:39,260
as species, is all we have.
只有与生俱来的东西

672
00:37:40,230 --> 00:37:42,620
The flaws that are out there are inevitable--
我们的缺陷不可避免

673
00:37:42,620 --> 00:37:44,550
they cannot be changed.
无法改变

674
00:37:45,530 --> 00:37:48,320
We need to accept them for what they are.
不论好坏 我们只能接受

675
00:37:48,950 --> 00:37:51,830
That's the only thing we can do with these flaws.
我们只能接受缺陷

676
00:37:51,830 --> 00:37:54,070
And people who have the constrained vision think
执有人性受约束的观点的人认为

677
00:37:54,070 --> 00:37:56,650
that our instincts, our inclinations,
我们的本能 欲望

678
00:37:56,650 --> 00:38:01,660
our basic nature is immutable, accepted.
我们的本性是永恒的 唯有接受

679
00:38:01,660 --> 00:38:06,230
And then what they do, rather than resign, they channel it.
但他们没有屈服 而是加以引导

680
00:38:06,230 --> 00:38:07,650
How do they channel it?
如何引导?

681
00:38:07,650 --> 00:38:10,030
By building certain political institutions
通过建立某种政治机构

682
00:38:10,030 --> 00:38:12,150
that would channel the flawed,
引导有缺陷的

683
00:38:12,150 --> 00:38:15,120
imperfect human nature toward the good.
不完美的人性向好的方面发展

684
00:38:16,400 --> 00:38:18,850
Philosophers and psychologists
执有这种观点的

685
00:38:19,140 --> 00:38:22,630
who fall under the constrained vision create them,
哲学家和心理学家创造了它们

686
00:38:22,930 --> 00:38:27,040
philosophies and psychologies and institutions and systems
创建了人生哲学 心理学 各种机构和体系

687
00:38:27,380 --> 00:38:31,840
to channel our flawed and imperfect nature.
来引导我们有缺点的不完美的人性

688
00:38:32,410 --> 00:38:36,890
People who fall under the constrained vision in the history of ideas,
在哲学史上认为人性受约束的人

689
00:38:37,210 --> 00:38:42,020
are people such as Alexander Hamilton, Adam Smith--
包括汉密尔顿 亚当斯密

690
00:38:42,320 --> 00:38:45,400
those of you are taking or will take EC 10,
学习经济学的都耳熟能详

691
00:38:47,260 --> 00:38:50,440
?, Fredrick Kayak.
Fredrick Kayak等

692
00:38:53,690 --> 00:38:55,500
These are people who say,
这些人认为

693
00:38:55,500 --> 00:38:57,340
"our nature is constrained.
"我们的本性是受约束的

694
00:38:57,340 --> 00:39:00,370
It's limited." Edmund Burke-- another one.
是有局限的" Edmund Burke说的

695
00:39:02,320 --> 00:39:04,130
What captures this idea best--
最准确阐述这种观点的

696
00:39:04,130 --> 00:39:06,250
the words of Francis Bacon,
是培根的话

697
00:39:06,780 --> 00:39:11,220
considered the father of the scientific movement,
他是17世纪时科学运动之父

698
00:39:11,220 --> 00:39:13,980
was a philosopher in 1600s:
是一名哲学家

699
00:39:13,980 --> 00:39:17,230
"Nature to be commanded must be obeyed."
"号令自然 必须遵守自然"

700
00:39:17,230 --> 00:39:22,090
Whether it's physical nature, or human nature.
不论是物质本质还是人性本质

701
00:39:22,400 --> 00:39:23,390
We need to obey it.
我们都需要遵守它

702
00:39:23,390 --> 00:39:25,460
It is what it is.
本质是不变的

703
00:39:25,460 --> 00:39:27,560
Now we have the unconstrained vision.
还有人性不受约束的观点

704
00:39:28,840 --> 00:39:31,000
Perhaps you are a little bit more optimistic,
也许你更乐观

705
00:39:31,760 --> 00:39:36,530
a little bit more utopian-- human nature can be improved.
更加乐天 人性可以改善

706
00:39:36,530 --> 00:39:37,580
It can be changed.
可以改变

707
00:39:37,580 --> 00:39:41,330
It is up to us to do so. It is perfectable.
取决于我们去不去做 本性可以完善

708
00:39:41,330 --> 00:39:44,510
We don't need to accept these flaws as inevitable.
不需要接受缺陷不可避免的观点

709
00:39:44,510 --> 00:39:46,180
We can perfect it.
可以完善它

710
00:39:46,970 --> 00:39:49,130
There are solutions to these flaws,
有办法解决这些缺陷

711
00:39:49,130 --> 00:39:53,010
to these imperfections and our role--
完善不完美的地方 我们的职责

712
00:39:53,010 --> 00:39:55,220
the goal of institutions,
机构的目标

