00:58:39,330 --> 00:58:41,870
Cognition-- thoughts.
认知代表思想

1072
00:58:43,510 --> 00:58:45,700
Unconditional acceptance,
无条件地接受

1073
00:58:46,000 --> 00:58:51,160
permission to be human relates primarily to our affect,
准许为人 主要与情感相关

1074
00:58:51,160 --> 00:58:52,710
to our emotions.
与情绪相关

1075
00:58:53,050 --> 00:58:57,280
They are there, just like the law of gravity is there.
它们是现实存在 就像万有引力定律

1076
00:58:57,610 --> 00:59:02,040
That does not mean we need to accept our behavior and our cognition.
那不代表我们要接受我们的行为和认知

1077
00:59:02,040 --> 00:59:05,600
For example, I can--
举个例子 我可以…

1078
00:59:05,600 --> 00:59:07,260
and having the past experience--
因为以前的经历

1079
00:59:07,260 --> 00:59:09,350
envy towards my best friend,
嫉妒我最好的朋友

1080
00:59:12,390 --> 00:59:15,780
that in and of itself does not make me a bad person.
那种情绪本身不代表我是个坏人

1081
00:59:16,380 --> 00:59:17,300
It's human.
这是人类本性

1082
00:59:17,300 --> 00:59:19,300
I've never met a person
我从没遇到过任何一个

1083
00:59:19,300 --> 00:59:21,490
who has never experienced or does not experience--
从来没有或没有体会过…

1084
00:59:21,490 --> 00:59:22,730
well, maybe the Dalai Lama--
也许达赖喇嘛可以

1085
00:59:22,730 --> 00:59:23,450
but other than that,
除了他

1086
00:59:23,450 --> 00:59:27,380
who does not experience envy toward other people.
谁都嫉妒过别人

1087
00:59:28,670 --> 00:59:30,600
And if it is true about the Dalai Lama,
如果说达赖喇嘛真的无欲无求

1088
00:59:30,600 --> 00:59:33,550
that is because he's worked on it for decades.
那也是修行几十年的结果

1089
00:59:34,470 --> 00:59:36,100
Envy is part of human nature--
嫉妒是人性的一部分

1090
00:59:36,100 --> 00:59:39,090
nothing good or bad about the envy.
嫉妒没有好坏之分

1091
00:59:39,090 --> 00:59:42,260
Nothing good or bad about experiencing the anger.
愤怒也无好坏之分

1092
00:59:42,670 --> 00:59:46,010
Nothing good or bad about experiencing the depression or anxiety.
抑郁和焦虑也无好坏之分

1093
00:59:46,580 --> 00:59:48,210
It's part of human nature.
那是人性的一部分

1094
00:59:48,470 --> 00:59:50,110
However, the question is,
问题在于

1095
00:59:50,110 --> 00:59:51,840
how do I choose to behave,
我要选择怎样的行为

1096
00:59:51,840 --> 00:59:54,140
to act as a result of it?
去表达情感？

1097
00:59:55,190 --> 00:59:57,810
That is where the moral domain enters.
道德在此介入

1098
00:59:57,810 --> 01:00:01,070
That's where I can have moral or immoral behavior
我可以选择道德和不道德的行为

1099
01:00:01,070 --> 01:00:06,550
toward my best friend or baby, or other people in general.
对待最好的朋友 孩子或一般人

1100
01:00:08,040 --> 01:00:10,430
I can still experience envy toward my best friend
我仍会嫉妒最好的朋友

1101
01:00:10,430 --> 01:00:15,820
and choose to behave generously and benevolently toward him.
但选择对他宽容和亲切

1102
01:00:16,720 --> 01:00:18,710
The same with cognition and we will talk a lot about it
认知也是如此 我们会深入讨论认知

1103
01:00:18,710 --> 01:00:22,160
when we talk about CBT-- Cognitive Behavioral Therapy.
当谈到认知行为治疗时

1104
01:00:24,540 --> 01:00:25,770
I can feel it certain way.
我可以感受它

1105
01:00:25,770 --> 01:00:26,710
But it doesn't mean that
但不代表

1106
01:00:26,710 --> 01:00:30,560
I need to resign to my thoughts about that feeling.
我要屈从于对那种感受的想法

1107
01:00:31,510 --> 01:00:34,280
Rumination is one of the things that we'll talk about a lot
我们会频繁谈到沉思

1108
01:00:34,280 --> 01:00:36,000
actually not that helpful--
其实沉思痛苦的情绪

1109
01:00:36,000 --> 01:00:38,710
to ruminate about painful emotions.
没有多大帮助

1110
01:00:39,290 --> 01:00:41,490
It's much helpful to write about them.
书写描述更有帮助

1111
01:00:41,490 --> 01:00:43,580
To talk to other people about them,
向别人倾诉更有帮助

1112
01:00:43,580 --> 01:00:45,540
rather than just be thinking constantly about
要胜过总是想着

1113
01:00:45,540 --> 01:00:48,000
how miserable I am because my girlfriend just left.
被女朋友甩了多么的惨

1114
01:00:48,000 --> 01:00:50,460
I haven't found anyone in Pinocchio's.
我还没在快餐店找到新目标

1115
01:00:53,980 --> 01:00:56,010
So rumination doesn't help.
沉思没有帮助

1116
01:00:56,010 --> 01:00:58,400
So I don't necessarily accept
我没有必要接受

1117
01:00:58,400 --> 01:01:00,810
all my irrational thoughts and again,
所有不理智的想法

1118
01:01:00,810 --> 01:01:02,630
we'll talk about it much more next week of
下周我们会更深入地探讨

1119
01:01:02,630 --> 01:01:07,300
how we can cognitively reframe what we were thinking.
如何认知性地重塑自己的想法

1120
01:01:07,300 --> 01:01:10,970
But the emotion-- that affect is the emotion,
但情绪 情感即情绪

1121
01:01:10,970 --> 01:01:12,260
it is what it is.
是无法改变的

1122
01:01:12,260 --> 01:01:16,230
And the key is to be true to reality,
重要的是要真实面对现实

1123
01:01:17,820 --> 01:01:20,350
which is also one of the main themes in the course.
这也是本门课的重要主题之一

1124
01:01:20,700 --> 01:01:24,430
In many ways, this course should not be called "Positive Psychology".
从很多方面来说这门课不该叫"积极心理学"

1125
01:01:24,980 --> 01:01:30,630
But I am telling you this after you already signed up for the class
我在你们选了这门课后才挑明

1126
01:01:30,630 --> 01:01:32,110
so it is too late to leave.
想退课也晚了

1127
01:01:32,240 --> 01:01:35,350
This is actually not a course on positive psychology.
这门课不是讲"积极心理学"

1128
01:01:35,350 --> 01:01:37,680
It's a course in reality psychology.
而是一门"现实心理学"课程

1129
01:01:38,300 --> 01:01:41,170
Because positive psychology may mean that
因为积极心理学可能表示

1130
01:01:41,170 --> 01:01:43,620
we are only focusing on the positive and what works,
我们只聚焦于积极的起作用的部分

1131
01:01:43,620 --> 01:01:45,660
ignoring all the rest that are not.
忽略其余不起作用的

1132
01:01:45,660 --> 01:01:48,740
Overdoing this class is shifting the pendulum.
我们要做的就像是改变钟摆幅度

1133
01:01:48,740 --> 01:01:54,070
So there is more even playing field instead of the 21:1 ratio,
比起21比1的比率 两方更均衡

1134
01:01:54,070 --> 01:01:58,190
we are doing much more, focusing on the positive.
我们做得更多 除了专注于积极的一面

1135
01:01:58,190 --> 01:01:59,640
And at the same time,
与此同时

1136
01:01:59,640 --> 01:02:02,030
accepting the painful emotions
也认同痛苦的情绪

1137
01:02:02,030 --> 01:02:05,350
are as much part of human nature as the wonderful emotions.
和美好的情绪一样都是人性的组成

1138
01:02:05,350 --> 01:02:07,910
And sooner we accept it, the better.
我们越早接受越好

1139
01:02:07,910 --> 01:02:10,960
That won't mean at the end of the course of 1504 or 100
那并不代表在1504课程结束后

1140
01:02:10,960 --> 01:02:12,940
or 100 other courses in the workshop
或修读完另外100门课程

1141
01:02:12,940 --> 01:02:14,580
and sold the books that you read,
然后就可以把读过的书丢了

1142
01:02:15,400 --> 01:02:17,780
it's not that you will not have painful emotions anymore.
并不是说 你就不会再感受到痛苦的情绪

1143
01:02:17,780 --> 01:02:22,100
It's simply your psychological immune system will become stronger,
只是你的心理免疫系统会变得更强

1144
01:02:22,100 --> 01:02:24,900
hopefully already by the end of this semester.
希望在本学期未就见成效

1145
01:02:24,900 --> 01:02:26,980
Psychological immune system will become stronger.
心理免疫系统会变得更强

1146
01:02:26,980 --> 01:02:29,530
And that means not that we don't get ill.
那不表示我们不再得病

1147
01:02:29,530 --> 01:02:33,420
It means we get ill less often and when we do get sick,
而是意味着我们更有抵抗力 即使得病

1148
01:02:33,420 --> 01:02:35,930
we'll recover more promptly.
也能很快康复

1149
01:02:35,930 --> 01:02:38,110
The difference between the extremely happy people
极其快乐的人和极其不快乐的人

1150
01:02:38,110 --> 01:02:44,880
and extremely unhappy people is not that one gets sad,
区别不是在于一个会伤心

1151
01:02:44,880 --> 01:02:46,720
of upset, or anxious, or depressed;
难过 焦虑或抑郁

1152
01:02:46,720 --> 01:02:47,960
and the other does not.
而另一个不会

1153
01:02:47,960 --> 01:02:49,330
Both groups do.
两类人都会

1154
01:02:50,340 --> 01:02:51,470
It's how quickly,
区别在于他们能够多么迅速

1155
01:02:51,470 --> 01:02:54,970
how promptly we can recover from these painful emotions--
多么快速地从痛苦情绪中恢复过来

1156
01:02:54,970 --> 01:02:57,950
in other words, how strong our psychological immune system is.
换言之 我们的心理免疫系统有多强

1157
01:02:57,950 --> 01:03:00,880
And our psychological immune system strengthens
我们的心理免疫系统会加强

1158
01:03:00,880 --> 01:03:05,300
when we give ourselves the permission to be human.
当我们准许自己为人时

1159
01:03:08,630 --> 01:03:10,640
Many of you've probably read this,
很多同学可能读到过这首诗

1160
01:03:10,640 --> 01:03:12,390
come across this, but I think this captures
听说过这首诗 它非常好地阐述了

1161
01:03:12,390 --> 01:03:17,230
so well the foundation of what it means to be actively accepting.
主动接受含义的基础

1162
01:03:17,680 --> 01:03:23,560
This has become the official mantra in many ways of the AA movement:
它已成为AA运动的正式圣言

1163
01:03:23,560 --> 01:03:27,130
"God, grant me the serenity to accept the things I cannot change;
"主啊 请赐我安详 接纳我不能改变的事物

1164
01:03:27,130 --> 01:03:29,660
the courage to change the things I can change;
请赐我勇气 去改变我可以改变的东西

1165
01:03:29,660 --> 01:03:32,300
and wisdom to know the difference."
并赐我智慧去认识这两者的差别"

1166
01:03:32,300 --> 01:03:33,710
The wisdom to know the difference--
认识两者差别的智慧

1167
01:03:33,710 --> 01:03:38,300
fortunately, a lot of this wisdom can come from studies,
幸运的是 这样的智慧可以通过学习获得

1168
01:03:38,300 --> 01:03:40,810
from research, from deep introspection that
通过研究和在这个学期

1169
01:03:40,810 --> 01:03:43,520
you will do throughout the semester.
进行的深刻反省中获得

1170
01:03:48,570 --> 01:03:53,140
What I want to do now is an exercise.
现在我想做个练习

1171
01:03:54,630 --> 01:03:57,510
I want to do a group meditation.
我想做一次群体冥想

1172
01:04:01,090 --> 01:04:02,040
Trying to understand,
希望你们理解

1173
01:04:02,040 --> 01:04:04,400
not just on the cognitive level of the research,
不只是在研究的认知层面上

1174
01:04:04,400 --> 01:04:08,290
but also to experience on the visceral emotional level,
还要在内心情感层面上去体会

1175
01:04:08,290 --> 01:04:17,880
what it really means to give ourselves the permission to be human.
准许自己为人的真正含义

1176
01:04:28,450 --> 01:04:30,580
Those of you who don't feel comfortable doing it,
感觉不自在的

1177
01:04:30,580 --> 01:04:31,850
you don't have to do it.
可以不参与

1178
01:04:31,850 --> 01:04:34,970
Those who feel comfortable to do it, do it.
认为没问题的 一起来做

1179
01:04:34,970 --> 01:04:36,970
If it's a stretch for you,
如果你觉得很勉强

1180
01:04:36,970 --> 01:04:38,180
I still recommend that you do it.
我仍建议你一起来

1181
01:04:38,180 --> 01:04:40,020
If you never meditate before,
如果你从没冥想过

1182
01:04:40,020 --> 01:04:44,260
this is a wonderful opportunity to do it for the first time.
这是你们尝试的好机会

1183
01:04:46,330 --> 01:04:47,530
One thing I do ask you:
我对你们的一个要求是

1184
01:04:47,530 --> 01:04:48,210
If you are not doing it,
如果你不做

1185
01:04:48,210 --> 01:04:50,180
if you don't participate,
不参与的同学

1186
01:04:50,180 --> 01:04:53,540
simply just keep quiet.
请保持安静

1187
01:04:53,540 --> 01:04:57,610
Other than that, I really do recommend that you join us.
此外 我强烈建议你参与

1188
01:04:58,230 --> 01:04:59,640
What I want to do together now
现在我要大家一起

1189
01:04:59,640 --> 01:05:05,430
is enter the realm of unconditional acceptance.
一起进入无条件接受境界

1190
01:05:06,370 --> 01:05:11,600
Se?or, just sit up straight as much as possible.
在座位上尽量坐直身体

1191
01:05:15,340 --> 01:05:25,300
If possible, your back relaxing against the back rest.
如果可以 后背在靠背上放松

1192
01:05:26,890 --> 01:05:30,130
Plant your feet comfortably on the floor.
双脚舒服地放在地板上

1193
01:05:34,390 --> 01:05:38,440
If you feel comfortable, close your eyes.
感觉舒适 闭上双眼

1194
01:05:47,860 --> 01:05:50,190
Shift the focus of your breath.
转移呼吸的焦点

1195
01:05:54,390 --> 01:06:00,550
Shift the focus of your thoughts to your breathing.
把思想的焦点 转移到呼吸上

1196
01:06:04,900 --> 01:06:09,400
Take a deep breath in all the way down to your belly.
向腹部深深吸气

1197
01:06:12,590 --> 01:06:14,630
And then breathe out.
然后呼气

1198
01:06:21,700 --> 01:06:23,750
Again, deep breath in;
再一次深深吸气

1199
01:06:26,520 --> 01:06:30,730
slow, gentle, quiet breath out.
缓慢 平稳 安静地呼气

1200
01:06:37,790 --> 01:06:40,940
Repeat that in silence.
安静地重复呼吸

1201
01:06:59,690 --> 01:07:05,640
If your mind wanders, simply bring it back to your breathing.
如果走神了 回到呼吸上

1202
01:07:07,360 --> 01:07:10,260
Deep, slow inhalation.
深深缓慢地吸气

1203
01:07:11,530 --> 01:07:16,000
Deep, slow, gentle, quiet exhalation.
深深缓慢 平稳 安静地呼气

1204
01:07:31,960 --> 01:07:35,160
Most of us don't breathe deeply enough.
多数人吸气的深度不够

1205
01:07:35,650 --> 01:07:42,540
We don't take the time to celebrate our breath,
我们没时间赞美我们的呼吸

1206
01:07:42,540 --> 01:07:44,840
our spirit, our being.
我们的精神 我们的存在

1207
01:07:46,610 --> 01:07:49,010
The connection, the link,
联系 关联

1208
01:07:49,010 --> 01:07:53,790
the bridge between our mind and our body;
心灵与身体的桥梁

1209
01:07:55,350 --> 01:07:59,020
between our emotions and our thoughts;
情绪和思想的桥梁

1210
01:08:03,480 --> 01:08:06,160
between the brain and the heart.
脑和心的桥梁

1211
01:08:11,360 --> 01:08:13,730
Continue with the deep breathing.
继续深呼吸

1212
01:08:27,570 --> 01:08:30,970
As you continue with the deep breath,
继续深呼吸的同时

1213
01:08:30,970 --> 01:08:35,840
shift your focus to your emotions, to your feelings.
将焦点转向情绪 转向感受

1214
01:08:41,010 --> 01:08:42,420
How are you doing?
你们好吗？

1215
01:08:43,950 --> 01:08:45,530
How are you feeling?
感觉如何？

1216
01:08:46,610 --> 01:08:49,650
Pay attention to your emotions.
注意你的情绪

1217
01:08:54,670 --> 01:08:59,150
Whatever they are, whatever it is that your feeling,
不论是怎样的情绪 不论感觉到什么

1218
01:09:00,230 --> 01:09:05,310
allow it to float through you. Naturally.
让它流过你的全身 自然地

1219
01:09:05,950 --> 01:09:10,770
Just experience your emotion whatever it is.
体会那种情绪

1220
01:09:20,540 --> 01:09:22,900
You may feel one emotion at one moment,
你可能先体会到一种情绪

1221
01:09:23,610 --> 01:09:26,520
different emotion the next. That's Ok.
然后又体会到另一种 这没关系

1222
01:09:27,900 --> 01:09:30,690
Whatever it is, accept it.
不论是怎么情绪 接受它

1223
01:09:30,690 --> 01:09:32,490
Experience it.
体会它

1224
01:09:33,620 --> 01:09:36,440
Give yourself the permission to be human.
准许自己为人

1225
01:09:38,460 --> 01:09:41,990
It's all OK. Just breath.
都没关系 呼吸

1226
01:09:59,310 --> 01:10:04,960
Continue to observe and experience whatever emotion comes up,
继续观察体会出现的情绪

1227
01:10:06,650 --> 01:10:10,270
whether it's calm or happiness,
不管是平静或快乐

1228
01:10:11,180 --> 01:10:17,320
whether it's anxiety, confusion, boredom or joy.
不管是焦虑 困惑 无聊或喜悦

1229
01:10:18,600 --> 01:10:20,070
Whatever it is,
不管它是什么

1230
01:10:23,410 --> 01:10:27,200
continue to breathe deeply into your belly.
继续向腹部深呼吸

1231
01:10:28,430 --> 01:10:33,580
And gently, slowly, quietly exhale.
平稳 缓慢 安静地呼气

1232
01:10:36,640 --> 01:10:40,330
Let the emotion flow just like the breath.
让那种情绪像呼吸一样流动

1233
01:10:57,320 --> 01:10:59,600
As you continue breathing deeply,
随着呼吸的加深

1234
01:11:00,960 --> 01:11:02,640
in your mind's eye,
用你的心眼

1235
01:11:03,590 --> 01:11:07,370
see yourself walking out of this classroom today,
看自己走出这间教室

1236
01:11:08,530 --> 01:11:10,360
walking in the yard,
走在校园里

1237
01:11:11,390 --> 01:11:14,710
with the feeling that all your feelings
体会你的所有感受

1238
01:11:15,420 --> 01:11:20,660
are real fine part of human nature.
都是人性的一部分

1239
01:11:22,460 --> 01:11:23,650
They just are.
它们在那里

1240
01:11:24,550 --> 01:11:26,630
Neither good nor bad.
不论好坏

1241
01:11:36,140 --> 01:11:40,020
As you walk amid the buildings and trees,
在你走在建筑物和树木之间时

1242
01:11:41,310 --> 01:11:44,390
as you see your friends and classmates,
在你看到朋友和同学时

1243
01:11:46,050 --> 01:11:49,560
allow these emotions to float through you,
让那些情绪流遍你的全身

1244
01:11:50,490 --> 01:11:53,420
freely, lightly.
自由地 轻盈地

1245
01:11:59,600 --> 01:12:02,100
By experiencing these emotions,
通过体会这些情绪

1246
01:12:02,450 --> 01:12:04,910
whether the ups and the downs,
不论是起是落

1247
01:12:05,460 --> 01:12:09,130
what you are doing is being,
